ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: 1. My friend and I spend all our free time together.
2. I can get into fights with my friend.
3. If I forgot my lunch or needed a little money my friend would loan it to me.
4. If other kids were bothering me my friend would help me.
5. If I have a problem at school or home I can talk to my friend about it.
6. If I said I was sorry after I had a fight with my friend they would still stay mad at me.
7. If my friend had to move away I would miss them.
8. When I do a good job at something my friend is happy for me.
9. My friend thinks of fun things for us to do together.
10. My friend can bug me or annoy me even though I ask them not to.
11. My friend helps me when I am having trouble with something.
12. My friend would stick up for me if another person was causing me trouble.
13. If there is something bothering me I can tell my friend about it even if it is something I cannot tell to other people.
14. If my friend or I do something that bothers the other one of us we can make up easily.
15. I feel happy when I am with my friend.
16. Sometimes my friend does things for me or makes me feel special.
17. My friend and I go to each other's houses after school and on weekends.
18. My friend and I can argue a lot.
19. My friend would help me if I needed it.
20. If my friend and I have a fight or argument we can say "I'm sorry" and everything will be alright.
21. I think about my friend even when my friend is not around.
22. Sometimes my friend and I just sit around and talk about things like school sports or things we like.
23. My friend and I disagree about many things.
FQS Total Raw Score
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: My friends talk to me about their thoughts and feelings.
Notes: 1 = Never; 2 = Seldom; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Nearly Always; 5 = Always; 999 = Prefer not to answer/missing

ElementDescription: My friends come to me for advice and assistance when they are troubled.
Notes: 2 = Never; 2 = Seldom; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Nearly Always; 5 = Always; 999 = Prefer not to answer/missing
